                          boolean valid,
                          java.util.Date validity)
        Internal constructor.

        Constructor based on all fields.

        Note: Should not be used. Use TrustedCertificate() instead.

        Parameters:
        accountId - The ID of the account.
        certificate - X509.v3 trusted certificate in PEM format.
        certificateFingerprint - A SHA-256 fingerprint of the certificate.
        createdAt - Creation UTC time RFC3339.
        description - Human readable description of this certificate.
        deviceExecutionMode - Device execution mode where 1 means a developer certificate.
        enrollmentMode - If true, signature is not required. Default value false.
        id - Entity ID.
        issuer - Issuer of the certificate.
        name - Certificate name.
        ownerId - The ID of the owner.
        service - Service name where the certificate is used.
        status - Status of the certificate.
        subject - Subject of the certificate.
        updatedAt - Last update UTC time RFC3339.
        valid - This read-only flag indicates whether the certificate is valid or not.
        validity - Expiration time in UTC formatted as RFC3339.
